my daughter is years old and doesnt know how to write her name what should i do i am a first grade teacher and i can tell you several fun ways to teacher her to write her name that will make her want to do it get a cookie sheet and some magnetic letters then help her arrange them in the correct order this will get her familiar with the order of the letters and the shapes of each letter she will use spray shaving cream on a table and allow her to trace her name in the cream kids love this have her trace it in sand it works the same way you didn't mention if your daughter is familiar with any of the letters of the alphabet yet if she is not it is going to be harder to teach her to write her name because this should come first there are several fun flash card games out there that you could use as you sing the abc's or you could play fun games with her where you write the letter and she guesses which one it is then have her do the same the most important thing is to remain patient and supportive no matter how frustrated you become if she sees that mom is annoyed with her progress or lack therof it will turn her off from trying and she will shut down good luck and feel free to contact me with any more questions The Adventures of Pete & Pete Pitaten Calvin and Hobbes Whose Line Is It Anyway? Mao (game) I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Game show Poker jargon Negima Little Britain Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Kodocha Good News Week Wheel of Fortune Winning Streak President (game) Hangul Amiga Power Social rule Floppy disk Counter-Strike Care Bears Milton H. Erickson Tag The Late Show with David Letterman Avenue Q CPU cache Beatmania IIDX The Shining (film) Kyle Broflovski Bubble Bobble American and British English differences Jumpstart 3rd Grade International Phonetic Alphabet Password (game) Joke Unidentified flying object Password Table tennis Our Gang Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Late N